name: OWLEX
description:
I never knew why I was afraid of
everything. I was always told that it
was "just in my head". Well, it turns
out it WAS just in my head. Literally.
The owls nested inside my brain
when I was 8 years old, and from that
point on, they controlled me. For a
while I wanted to stop them. I wanted
to get them out of my brain. But
eventually I realized that I like who I
am, and I am who I am, in part,
BECAUSE of these brain-owls. So I
let them stay. And now, we are one.
Traditional pen & ink + watercolor
and digital painting.
